## Admin Dashboard UI Conventions

### Design Language

Admin dashboards are **functional, not beautiful**. Optimize for information density and scan-ability.

**Colors:**
- ✅ **Green:** Passing target (e.g., PMF score ≥40%)
- ⚠️ **Yellow:** Below target but not critical
- ❌ **Red:** Critical / failing

**Typography:**
- Large numbers for key metrics (`text-5xl font-bold`)
- Small labels (`text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-stone-600`)
- Monospace for emails, IDs, codes

**Layout:**
- Cards for individual metrics (2-col or 3-col grid)
- Tables for drill-down (sortable, filterable)
- No marketing fluff (no hero images, no testimonials)

### Metric Card Pattern

```typescript
// Reusable component for admin metrics

interface MetricCardProps {
  label: string;
  value: number | string;
  target?: number;
  unit?: string;
  passing?: boolean;
}

function AdminMetricCard({ label, value, target, unit, passing }: MetricCardProps) {
  const displayValue = typeof value === 'number' 
    ? `${value.toFixed(1)}${unit ?? ''}` 
    : value;
  
  const badgeColor = passing 
    ? 'bg-green-100 text-green-700' 
    : 'bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700';

  return (
    <div className="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-xl p-8">
      <div className="flex items-start justify-between mb-6">
        <div>
          <h2 className="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">
            {label}
          </h2>
          {target && (
            <p className="text-sm text-stone-600">
              Target: {target}{unit ?? ''}
            </p>
          )}
        </div>
        {passing !== undefined && (
          <div className={`inline-flex px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-xs font-semibold ${badgeColor}`}>
            {passing ? 'On Track' : 'Below Target'}
          </div>
        )}
      </div>

      <div className="flex items-baseline gap-2">
        <div className={`font-serif text-5xl font-bold ${
          passing ? 'text-green-600' : 'text-yellow-600'
        }`}>
          {displayValue}
        </div>
        {target && (
          <div className="text-stone-500">/ {target}{unit ?? ''}</div>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Usage:**

```typescript
<AdminMetricCard
  label="PMF Score"
  value={pmfScore}
  target={40}
  unit="%"
  passing={pmfScore >= 40}
/>
```

