## Deployment Checklist for New Admin Feature

When adding a new admin page or metric:

- [ ] API route has role check (`user.role !== 'admin'` → 403)
- [ ] Page uses `DashboardNav` (not `PublicNav`)
- [ ] Metric card shows target comparison (green/yellow indicator)
- [ ] Drill-down table for investigating outliers
- [ ] Error states handled (unauthorized, no data, API down)
- [ ] Loading states shown (spinner, skeleton, or "Loading...")
- [ ] No sensitive PII exposed (emails in admin view are OK, user IDs preferred)
- [ ] Aggregation queries are cached (hourly or daily)
- [ ] Build test passes (`npm run build`)

