## Anti-Patterns

### ❌ Exposing Admin Data in Public APIs
```typescript
// Bad: No role check
export async function GET() {
  return NextResponse.json({ allUserEmails: [...] });
}
```

Always gate with `user.role !== 'admin'`.

### ❌ Real-Time Queries for Historical Data
```typescript
// Bad: Scans entire table on every page load
const allSurveys = await prisma.pmfSurvey.findMany();
const pmfScore = calculateScore(allSurveys);
```

Cache it. PMF score from 6 hours ago is fine for an admin dashboard.

### ❌ Putting Admin Links in Public Nav
```typescript
// Bad: Leaks admin URLs to non-admins
<PublicNav>
  <Link href="/admin/growth">Metrics</Link>
</PublicNav>
```

Admin links only appear in `DashboardNav`, only when `role === 'admin'`.

